reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars All natural, biodegradable and soft but durable fabric
reviews.reviewText: I was reluctant to use these due to the mass production focus of Kirkland products but I did a bit of research. Tencel, the fabric cannot be flushed but it is biodegradable (lyocell fiber is the technical name and it's made from wood pulp or cellulose). The other natural and unscented ingredients are no different than products like 7th generation. The price is good. What I like the most is that the Tencel material does not pill up and leave any pills or fabric residue on your skin even if you use it on rough surfaces of your body (i.e. hair or razor stubble). Unfortunately this is a problem I have found with other brands. This is important to me since I use them on myself and adults, not on the soft hairless skin of a baby.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 16, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The only wipes you want!
reviews.reviewText: Best wipes ever! They come in a huge pack, so it takes FOREVER to run out. That's great not just for me, but for when I need to drop off wipes at daycare. They're thick, soft, but always moist (I wasn't sure how moist they'd stay by the time you get to the bottom of the pack, but they do!). They don't irritate gentle baby skin. They also work great also on messy sticky faces and hands.The only wipes I buy. Forget the name brands - not worth it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Two tiny thumbs up!
reviews.reviewText: This is just an outstanding baby wipe! Before, when I would ask my baby to wipe the table or the counter he would complain that the wipes I used to get were too big for his tiny little hands and he would often get entangled in them that the table and counter would never get cleaned. But the Kirkland Signature Baby Wipes are small enough for him to hold that the table and counter are cleaned in no time at all, especially when he can hold one wipe in each hand!
